The paper discusses the use of statistical and online learning theory to reason about application-specific algorithm selection, which suggests that it belongs to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions empirical performance models and self-improving algorithms, which are commonly used in data science (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the complexity of classes of functions, which is relevant to computational complexity theory (cs.CC).
